      },
      "date": "2013-10-22 08:23:10.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 4:\n\n> Tests received by maloo, run on CentOS release 6.4/x86_64: (https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sessions/316786f0-3a62-11e3-aede-52540035b04c). Ran 16 tests. 1 tests failed: conf-sanity.\n\nconf-sanity test 78 failed as follows:\n\n CMD: client-13vm4 resize2fs  /dev/lvm-OSS/S1 49124\n client-13vm4: resize2fs 1.42.7.wc1 (12-Apr-2013)\n client-13vm4: resize2fs: New size smaller than minimum (53248)\n client-13vm4: \n  conf-sanity test_78: @@@@@@ FAIL: shrink fs2ost to 49124 failed\n\nAfter the filesystem was expanded to the LV device size, the minimum size of the filesystem detected by resize2fs was also changed to the LV device size, which caused the filesystem cannot be shrunk. However, this issue does not exist on physical device, and the same conf-sanity test 78 passed on physical device: https://maloo.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1b8f449a-3af2-11e3-a32e-52540035b04c\n\nI'll update the patch to check the minimum size so as to decide whether to do shrink or not.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 4
    },
